# Execution Constitution (Growrixos)

Ported essentials from `DOC/Universal/Execution Constitution.md`. Governs documentation vs implementation and Agent Brain discipline.

## Three layers (never mix stages)

| Layer | Paths | Purpose |
|-------|-------|---------|
| Universal | `DOC/Universal/` | Reusable prompts, roles, enterprise guides |
| Project plan | `DOC/PROJECT PLAN/` | Generated project-specific docs — SSOT for `web/` SaaS implementation |
| Code | `web/`, `sites/`, `Frontend_Nextjs/` | Implementation surfaces |

## Two execution stages

### Stage A — Documentation generation

- Entry: universal orchestration prompts, blueprint factory
- Output: docs under `DOC/PROJECT PLAN/` or `blueprints/`
- **No code implementation**

### Stage B — Implementation

- Entry: `DOC/PROJECT PLAN/ai-context.yaml` (SaaS) or lane skill (templates/migrations)
- **Never restart from universal prompts** once project docs exist

## Materialization gate

Before updating any execution ledger:

1. Planning artifact must exist on disk (`*-e2e-plan.md`, `CONVERSION-MAP.md`, scope doc, or blueprint deliverable)
2. Affected role-specific docs materialized in owning folders when applicable
3. Chat summaries are **never** canonical — disk artifacts are

## Agent Brain read order

Resolve lane via [`.cursor/brain/lane-router.yaml`](.cursor/brain/lane-router.yaml), then read in order:

| Lane | Brain | Ledger |
|------|-------|--------|
| `web/` | `memories/repo/site-brain.md` | `DOC/PROJECT PLAN/Tasks/tasks.md` |
| `sites/` | `.cursor/brain/template-brain.md` | `.cursor/execution/template-tasks.md` |
| `Frontend_Nextjs/` | `.cursor/brain/migration-brain.md` | `.cursor/execution/template-tasks.md` |
| Conversion | `.cursor/brain/migration-brain.md` | `.cursor/execution/template-tasks.md` |

## Session recovery

On resume or `/resume-brain`:

1. Read `lane-router.yaml`
2. Read lane brain + ledger
3. Read controlling skill or `ai-context.yaml`
4. Continue from last `in_progress` or `not_started` task — do not re-plan from chat memory

## Gate failure protocol

STOP → DEBUG → FIX → RE-RUN applicable validations before continuing or declaring complete.

## Task ledger

All material work uses `@task-ledger` discipline. SaaS: `DOC/PROJECT PLAN/Tasks/tasks.md`. Templates/migrations: `.cursor/execution/template-tasks.md`.
